Installation:
- sudo apt-get install git-all

Create repository:
- git init : creates a local repository
- git clone URL : clones an existing repository from a server (e.g. GitHub.com)

Save a change:
- git add (--all or filename) : prepares file to be stored in repository
- git commit (-m 'Note') : saves prepared files in the repository

Handling with repositories on servers:
- git pull : retrieves the repository from server
- git push : updates the repository on the server
